Description: Striker 300ST by Kramer Candy Apple Red EMG Project Electric Guitar Click images to enlarge Description Striker 300ST by Kramer Candy Apple Red EMG Project Guitar (80's)   This will guitar is great for someone looking for a project. Looks like this guitar has been modified with EMG Pickups. Ok condition is "ok" needs some work. It is easy to tell this guitar has been stored for a while unplayed. I replaced the battery and guitar electronics are working, some static mostly from the input jack, a litte noise on the knobs not much. Tremolo feels good, neck is straight. Will need new strings, fret polish, and probably new input jack. The pickups are bright and punch (love emg) String height might be considered a little hight to some, but to me its plays fine. No string buzz (strings on it now are rusted so that's impressive). Cosmetically there are a couple nicks in the paint, nothing major. A hole in the pickguard (probably modification later removed) Not sure of year, I'm guessing mid 1980's. This is a great project for someone who enjoy's working on guitars.  Case is included.
